{"questionId":"9083790","questionHtml":"<p>An object of mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> is launched from the surface of the Earth. The Earth has a mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> and&nbsp;radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>. The acceleration due to gravity at the surface of the Earth is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math>. What is the escape&nbsp;speed of the object from the surface of the Earth?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>r</mi></msqrt></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9083790","referenceCode":"22M.1A.HL.TZ1.33","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"An object of mass m is launched from the surface of the Earth. The Earth has a mass M and radius r. The acceleration due to gravity at the surface of the Earth is g. What is the es","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"33","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D.1 Gravitational fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}